<html
    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
    xml:lang="en"
    lang="en"
    metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
    i18n:domain="launchpad">

<body>

<metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_one">
  <div class="portlet">
    <h4>About Soyuz:</h4>

    <div class="portletBody portletContent">
      <img src="/++resource++info_icon.gif" />
      "Soyuz" is the part of Launchpad that keeps track of the applications
      published in different distributions. It allows you to track, for
      example, the bugs in a distribution.
    </div>
  </div>
</metal:leftportlets>

<metal:rightportlets fill-slot="portlets_two">
  <div class="portlet">
    <h4>About Read-Only Distributions:</h4>

    <div class="portletBody portletContent">
      <img src="/++resource++info_icon.gif" />
      Some of these distributions are read-only.
      They can be browsed in Launchpad, but not altered or managed,
      and their information might be out of date.
    </div>
  </div>
</metal:rightportlets>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

    <p class="documentDescription">
      This page shows all distributions that are registered in the
      Launchpad.
    </p>

    <table width="100%" class="listing">
        <tr>
            <th>Name</th>
            <th>Title</th>
            <th>Domain Name</th>
        </tr>
        <tr tal:repeat="distribution context"
            tal:attributes="onclick
                string:window.location='/distros/${distribution/name}'">
            <td>
                <a tal:content="distribution/name" 
	               tal:attributes="href
                       distribution/name">
	               distribution name
	            </a>
                <span tal:condition="python: distribution.name in ['redhat', 'debian', 'gentoo']">
                    *
                </span>
            </td>
            <td tal:content="distribution/title">
                distribution title
            </td>
            <td tal:content="distribution/domainname">
                domain.org
            </td>
        </tr>
    </table>    

    <div>
      <div style="float: right;">
        (<span tal:replace="view/count" />
        distributions in total)
      </div>
      <div style="float: left;">
        * read-only distribution.
      </div>
    </div>


  </div>

</body>
</html>
